OL,5,FWHEN 1NT IS DOUBLED by Andrew Kambites 
OL,7,GIf your partner'sF1NTGis doubled, you  
OL,8, will rarely have enough to redouble for
OL,9, blood. Therefore it is common to use   
OL,10, redouble conventionally to give you    
OL,11, more opportunities to escape fromF1NT  
OL,12, doubled. It is effective to play that  
OL,13, redouble compels opener to bidF2C.GThen
OL,14, you can either pass (if your suit is   
OL,15, clubs) or sign off in your suit.       
OL,17, This releases 2-level bid to show two- 
OL,18, suiters, the suit bid and a higher suit
OL,19,Gwith at least a 4-4 shape.       >>>>  
